# ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
# ║              DEAL SYSTEM — FRONTEND ENVIRONMENT                      ║
# ║  1. Copy this file:  cp .env.example .env.local                      ║
# ║  2. Fill in your values below                                        ║
# ║  3. Start frontend:  npm run dev                                     ║
# ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

# Backend API base URL (no trailing slash)
# Development: http://localhost:5000
# Production:  https://your-backend-domain.onrender.com
#
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT FOR VERCEL DEPLOYMENT:
#   This file is a template. Do NOT copy it to .env.local with localhost.
#   In Vercel dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables, set:
#     NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL = https://deal-system-backend.onrender.com
#   (Next.js bakes NEXT_PUBLIC_ vars at BUILD TIME — wrong URL = silent failure)

# Local development:
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:5000

# Production (set this in Vercel dashboard, not here):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://deal-system-backend.onrender.com
